Design

General

The code should be as strongly typed as possible, making it clear through its design how the integration points are expected to interact.

Reactive Streams

The Reactive Streams API is being used to reflect the asynchronous nature of communication with the server. However, in the currently implementation, its usage is highly synchronous.

When/if this migrates to JDK 9, this will likely change to use the standard Flow interfaces.

Checker Framework

This uses the Checker Framework to add much better type checking (including making the use of null actually safe and useful).

There are no runtime implications (besides safer code).

Checker Framework

This uses Project Lombok to get rid of massive amounts of Java boilerplate.

There are no runtime implications (besides safer code). When developing you probably want to use the "Lombok" plugin for your IDE, but it’s not required. The Gradle idea task will take care of making sure everything is "hooked up" correctly for IntelliJ IDEA.

Releasing

./gradlew release -Prelease.scope=patch -Prelease.stage=final

See the release plugin documentation
